pullsbody:
Fixes #84


As of January 1 2019, Mozilla requires that all GitHub projects include this [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](https://github.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) file in the project root. The file has two parts:

1. Required Text - All text under the headings *Community Participation Guidelines and How to Report*, are required, and should not be altered.
2. Optional Text - The Project Specific Etiquette heading provides a space to speak more specifically about ways people can work effectively and inclusively together. Some examples of those can be found on the [Firefox Debugger](https://github.com/devtools-html/debugger.html/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) project, and [Common Voice](https://github.com/mozilla/voice-web/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). (The optional part is commented out in the [raw template file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md), and will not be visible until you modify and uncomment that part.)

If you have any questions about this file, or Code of Conduct policies and procedures, please see [Mozilla-GitHub-Standards](https://wiki.mozilla.org/GitHub/Repository_Requirements) or email Mozilla-GitHub-Standards+CoC@mozilla.com.

_(Message COC002)_
pull_commit_message:
Add Mozilla Code of Conduct file

Fixes #84.

_(Message COC002)_

pullsbody:
Phew! This adds decent support for keyboard navigation to the canvas parts of the site. There's some things missing, primarily:
- The styling of the site makes it hard to tell where the keyboard is currently focused on the non-canvas parts of the site.
- The scrolling on the checklist view when you tab between items is really choppy, but the scrolling math there is so complicated that I didn't think it worth it to delay this PR any further before I figured it out properly.

Since this site is so complicated, I'll leave some comments on the diff explaining some things.

This should be deployed on http://lorax.mkelly.me/ within a few minutes of this PR being up.

pullsbody:
Fixes the issues with the site not running on Linux but using autoDetectRenderer to allow use of WebGL on Linux instead of Canvas. Tested using an Ubuntu VirtualBox.

Also has some minor JSHint / whitespace fixes.
pull_commit_message: JSHint fixes.

pullsbody:
Fixes the issues with the site not running on Linux but using autoDetectRenderer to allow use of WebGL on Linux instead of Canvas. Tested using an Ubuntu VirtualBox.

Also has some minor JSHint / whitespace fixes.
pull_commit_message:
Fix bug 1113339: Use autoDetectRenderer instead of CanvasRenderer.

The autoDetectRenderer detects whether WebGL is supported and, if it is,
uses that for rendering graphics instead of Canvas.

In theory this is a performance boost, but the big win for us is that it
happens to also fix the rendering issues on Linux. Yay!
